ces to be provided by Deductive Limited under the Contract</li><li><strong>VAT</strong> means value added tax chargeable under English Law for the time being and any similar additional tax</li></ul><p>1.2 Headings in these terms and conditions shall not affect their interpretation.</p><p>1.3 A person includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (whether or not having a separate legal entity).</p><p>1.4 A reference to a statute or statutory provision is a reference to it as it is in force for the time being, taking account of any amendment, extension or re-enactment and includes any subordinate legislation or the time being in force made under it.</p><p>1.5 A reference to writing or written includes faxes and email.</p><p><strong>2. Application of Terms and Conditions</strong></p><p>2.1 These terms and conditions shall:</p><p>2.1.1 apply to and be incorporated into the Contract; and</p><p>2.1.2 prevail over any inconsistent terms or conditions contained, or referred to, in the Customer’s purchase order, confirmation of order, acceptance of a Statement of Work or specification or other Document supplied by the Customer, or implied by law, trade custom, practice or course of dealing.</p><p>2.2 The Customer’s acceptance of the Statement of Work for Services by Deductive Limited, constitutes the Contract to provide the Services in the Statement of Work, or by Deductive Limited starting to provide the Services, in which case a contract shall be established on these terms and conditions.</p><p>2.3 Statement of Works are given by Deductive Limited on the basis that no contract shall come into existence except in accordance with condition 2.2. Any Statement of Work is valid for a period of 30 days from the date given, provided it has not been previously withdrawn.</p><p><strong>3. Commencement and Duration</strong></p><p>3.1 Subject to condition 13, the Services supplied under the Contract shall commence on the date of the Customer’s acceptance of the Statement of Work and continue unless the Contract is terminated by one of the parties giving to the other not less than 6 months’ written notice.</p><p><strong>4. Implementation of Contract</strong></p><p>4.1 In return for payment of the Fees, Deductive Limited shall perform the Services using reasonable skill and care of a competent provider of similar services and in accordance with the Specification.</p><p>4.2 Deductive Limited shall use its reasonable endeavours to meet any performance dates specified in the Statement of Work but any such dates shall be estimates only and time shall not be of the essence.</p><p><strong>5. Customer’s Obligations</strong></p><p>5.1 The Customer shall </p><p>5.1.1 co-operate with Deductive in all matters relating to the Statement of Work;</p><p>5.1.2 provide all information, Documents, access and assistance as is reasonably necessary to enable Deductive Limited to provide the Services;</p><p>5.1.3 shall pay the Fees in accordance with condition 6 below.</p><p><strong>6. Fees</strong></p><p>6.1 In consideration of the Services the Customer shall pay the Fees as set out in the Statement of Work.</p><p>6.2 The Fees shall be paid to Deductive Limited without deduction or set-off and Deductive Limited shall invoice the Customer for the charges that are then payable unless otherwise stated on the Statement of Work.</p><p>6.3 The Customer shall pay the Fees within 30 days of the date of the invoice received.</p><p>6.4 If Deductive Limited do not receive payment by the due date then it may charge the Customer interest in accordance with the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998, and may suspend all Services until payment is made in full.</p><p>6.5 The parties agree that Deductive Limited may review and increase the charges as set out in the Statement of Work in accordance with the UK Retail Prices Index (RPI) provided that the Fees shall only be subject to an increase on each anniversary. Unless otherwise notified by Deductive Limited, the rates and prices which make up the Fees shall be adjusted on each anniversary of the date of the Statement of Work by the annual movement in the latest available UK RPI excluding Mortgage Interest Rates published by the UK Office for National Statistics.</p><p><strong>7. Intellectual Property Rights</strong></p><p>7.1 Prior to complete payment of the Fees, any Intellectual Property relating to the Services and any derivative works shall remain exclusively owned by Deductive.</p><p>7.2 Upon complete payment of the Fees, any Intellectual Property relating to the Services and any derivative works shall be transferred by Deductive to the Customer.8.</p><p><strong>8. Warranties</strong></p><p>8.1 For the term of the Contract Deductive Limited warrants to the Customer:</p><p>8.1.1 the Services will conform to the specification on the Statement of Work and undertakes to remedy any material defects or deficiencies following notification by the Customer;</p><p>8.1.2 that it has the skill and expertise to enter into the Contract;</p><p>8.1.3 that it will be in the position to continue to support the Services provided under the Contract.</p><p><strong>9. Limitation of Liability</strong></p><p>9.1 This condition sets out the entire liability of Deductive Limited (including any liability for acts or omissions of its employees, agents, consultants, and subcontractors) to the Customer in respect of:</p><p>9.1.1 breach of Contract;</p><p>9.1.2 any use made by the Customer of the Services, Deliverables, or any part of them; and</p><p>9.1.3 any representation, statement, or tortious act or omission (including negligence).</p><p>9.2 Nothing in these terms and conditions limits or excludes liability of Deductive Limited for personal injury or death resulting from negligence or for any damage or liability incurred by the Customer as a result of fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation by Deductive Limited.</p><p>9.3 Subject to conditions 9.1 and 9.2 Deductive shall not be liable for loss of profit, loss or business, depletion of goodwill and/or similar losses, loss of anticipated savings, loss of goods, loss of contracts, loss of use, loss of data or information, or any special, indirect, consequential, or pure economic loss, costs, damages, charges or expenses.</p><p>9.4 Deductive Limited’s total liability arising in connection with the performance, or contemplated performance of the Contract shall be limited to the Fees.</p><p><strong>10. Confidentiality and publicity</strong></p><p>10.1 Each Party shall treat as confidential all information howsoever disclosed by the other in connection with the Contract and shall use such information only for purposes directly connected with this terms and conditions and only disclose confidential information to persons under its control who need to know such information for the purposes of the Contract and subject to the disclosing Party ensuring that such persons are aware of and comply with the provisions of this clause. Confidential information excludes any information which the receiving Party already knew or had rightfully possession of before the commencement of the negotiations leading to the Contract; or which was already public knowledge or becomes so at a future date (except as a result of a breach of this clause). These obligations survive termination of this Agreement.</p><p>10.2 Each Party acknowledges that the other’s confidential information may constitute a vital business asset and that in the event of breach of the above confidentiality undertakings, the aggrieved Party reserves its right to damages and alternative remedies, including but not limited to injunctive relief.</p><p>10.3 Notwithstanding clause 10.1, Deductive Limited shall be entitled to include the Customer and its logo on its list of customers and partners but shall obtain the Customer’s prior written agreement to any publicity which mentions the Contract or the Customer. The Customer shall not unreasonably withhold or delay its written agreement.</p><p><strong>11. Term and termination</strong></p><p>11.1 Either Party may terminate the Contract by notice to the other if the other:</p><p>11.1.1 is in material breach of any term, condition or provision of this Agreement or of any provision required by law or persistently commits a lesser breach and fails to remedy any such breach within thirty days of receiving notice of such breach; or</p><p>11.1.2 presents a petition or has a petition presented by a creditor for its winding up, or calls a meeting to pass a resolution for voluntary winding up, or enters into any liquidation (other than for the purposes of a bona fide reconstruction or amalgamation), or calls a meeting of its creditors, or has a receiver appointed for any of its undertakings or assets, or is deemed by any relevant statutory provisions to be unable to pay its debts.</p><p>11.2 Upon termination of the Contract all rights and obligations of the Parties shall automatically cease except for such rights of action that have accrued prior to such termination and any rights or obligations under these terms and conditions or at law, which expressly or by implication are intended to come into or continue in force upon termination. </p><p>11.3 Where Deductive Limited terminates the Contract, the Customer shall disable all copies of the Software. </p><p><strong>12. Non-solicitation</strong></p><p>12.1 For the term of the Contract and for twelve months thereafter, the Customer shall not directly or indirectly solicit the services or employment of any Deductive Limited personnel. This provision does not apply where Deductive Limited personnel make unsolicited approaches to the Customer or respond to any public recruitment campaign.</p><p><strong>13. Data Protection</strong></p><p>13.1 The Customer acknowledges and agrees that the data collected by Deductive Limited will be processed by and on behalf of Deductive Limited in connection with the Services.</p><p>13.2 Deductive Limited shall comply with the UK Data Protection Act 1998 (“the DPA”) and in particular, but without limitation shall:</p><p>13.2.1 ensure that information is obtained and processed fairly and lawfully and shall ensure that part 1 of Schedule 1 of the DPA is complied with at all times;</p><p>13.2.2 obtain and maintain all appropriate notifications required under the DPA and ensure that its notification details include all persons purposes and other particulars required to be notified under the DPA in connection with this terms and conditions; and</p><p>13.2.3 ensure that appropriate technical and organisational measures are taken against unauthorised or unlawful processing of personal data and against accidental loss or destruction of, or damage to, personal data.</p><p>13.3 The Customer shall obtain such written permissions from its clients as may be required by local law in respect of the data and the rights as set out above.</p><p>13.4 In the event that there are companies to whom Deductive Limited should not sell the anonymous data, the Customer shall provide details to Deductive Limited.</p><p>13.5 Deductive Limited shall inform the Customer immediately if an enforcement notice under the DPA is served on it.</p><p><strong>14. Dispute resolution</strong></p><p>14.1 Except for interim injunctive remedies, the chief executive of each Party or their nominees will have thirty days to resolve any dispute before either Party may resort to any other course of action.</p><p><strong>15. Assignment</strong></p><p>15.1 Neither Party may assign or transfer all or part of the Contract, or any of its rights or obligations or appoint any agent to perform such obligations without the other’s prior written agreement. However, by giving the other not less than sixty days’ notice, either Party may transfer all of its rights and obligations to a wholly owned subsidiary, or to a wholly owned subsidiary of its parent company, or to its parent company. </p><p><strong>16. Waiver</strong></p><p>16.1 Failure by either Party to enforce any of the provisions of this Agreement will not be a waiver of such rights and will not affect the validity of the Contract nor affect that Party\'s rights to take subsequent action.</p><p><strong>17. Severability</strong></p><p>17.1 If any competent authority finds any part of these terms and conditions to be invalid, unlawful or unenforceable, the Contract will be deemed to be amended to the extent required to remove the competent authority’s findings but so as to allow the rest of the Contract to remain valid and unaffected to the fullest possible extent.</p><p><strong>18. Force majeure</strong></p><p>18.1 Except for the obligation to make payments properly due, neither Party will be liable for delay or failure to perform obligations caused by circumstances beyond its reasonable control, provided that the affected Party promptly gives the other notice of such delay or failure and circumstances and that the affected Party uses reasonable endeavours to mitigate the delay or failure.</p><p><strong>19. Notices</strong></p><p>19.1 All notices or written agreements mentioned in these terms and conditions shall be given as follows:</p><p>19.1.1 by delivery-recorded mail or courier to the authorised representative of the other Party at any address shown in the Contract, or to any other address that one Party has notified the other of, and will be valid on the date of recorded receipt, or</p><p>19.1.2 by fax to the authorised representative of the other Party and will be valid at the time shown on a successful transmission report, or</p><p>19.1.3 by email to the email address of the authorised representative of the other Party and will be valid at the time of sending but will not be deemed served if the email system has generated an unsuccessful transmission or unsuccessful delivery report.</p><p><strong>20. Legal construction</strong></p><p>20.1 No term of the Contract is enforceable by any person who is not a party to it whether relating to the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999 or otherwise. </p><p>20.2 The Contract and these terms and conditions are governed by English law and subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts. The United Nations’ Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods does not apply to this Agreement.</p><p>20.3 The Contract represents the entire agreement and understanding between the Parties in respect of its subject matter. Any terms and conditions of any purchase orders, acknowledgements or receipts issued by the Customer in connection with the Contract will have no effect even if they contain statements to the contrary and it is understood that Deductive Limited will accept any such purchase orders, acknowledgements or receipts subject to these terms and conditions only.</p>');
